<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-90-1604 </DOCNO><TEXT>Different concepts of distance between states for the use of statisticaldeduction when describing changes in states, for measurements, in particular,are studied. A modified expression for the distance is suggested andthe shape of final states is obtained using it. It is shown that ''thermodynamicdistance'', determined by relative entropy, is more approximate thanthe statistical ones.</TEXT></DOC>